OL,6,FRecipients include people who can't
OL,7,Fwalk unaided or are unable to put a
OL,8,Fmeal in the microwave.
OL,10,FThe council say the service is
OL,11,Fdesigned to "help people maintain
OL,12,Ftheir independence and provide a
OL,13,Fregular check-in to ensure that all is
OL,14,Fwell in the household".
OL,16,FMargaret Rees, 87, who lives in
OL,17,FPenybryn, says she has no family left
OL,18,Fand describes her once-a-day contact
OL,19,Fwith a staff member from the meals on
OL,20,Fwheels service as her "lifeline".
